qas.question: What church do 90% of Christian minority in Egypt belong?
Where are other Non-native Christian communities found?

answers.text: urban regions of Cairo and Alexandria
Greek Catholic, Greek Orthodox, and Maronite Catholic denominations

context: Of the Christian minority in Egypt over 90% belong to the native <a0_0>Coptic Orthodox Church<a0_0/> of Alexandria, an Oriental Orthodox Christian Church. Other native Egyptian Christians are adherents of the Coptic Catholic Church, the Evangelical Church of Egypt and various other Protestant denominations. Non-native Christian communities are largely found in the <a1_0>urban regions of Cairo and Alexandria<a1_0/>, such as the Syro-Lebanese, who belong to <a2_0>Greek Catholic, Greek Orthodox, and Maronite Catholic denominations<a2_0/>.
